Description: Nuovo soggettario (NS)- edited by the National Central Library of Florence- is the Italian subject indexing tool for various types of resources. It has been developed in compliance with the IFLA recommendations- and other international standards in the field of subject indexing. This tool has been created for general and specialized Italian libraries- and for museums- multimedia libraries- archives and documentation centres. The main component of the NS is a general thesaurus available on the web since 2007 (http://thes.bncf.firenze.sbn.it/ricerca.php). The thesaurus comprises nowadays approximately 69.400 terms and it is updated on a regular basis.All metadata can be used- in accordance with Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 licence.
Sources: Web:http://thes.bncf.firenze.sbn.it/ Name:BNCF - settore Ricerche e strumenti di indicizzazione semantica Email:bnc-fi.nuovosoggettario@beniculturali.it
